Chinese ambassador to Kenya Wu Peng  yesterday assured former Prime Minister Raila Odinga of China’s support for the construction of Standard Gauge Railway to Kisumu and Busia.  He added that the Mombasa-Nairobi SGR is making good financial progress towards breaking even. The envoy said this when he paid  Raila a courtesy call at his Capitol Hill offices. The two held discussions that centred on strengthening ties between China and Africa. They singled out trade, culture and infrastructure development as areas with potential for more collaboration. Raila  urged China to partner with Kenya in developing modern sports facilities. He further asked for support in development of Kenya’s maritime transport sector to boost regional trade and investment in development of Special Economic Zones across the country.